		<Version>4.9.5-local.13</Version>
		<PackageReleaseNotes>v4.9.5-local.13: WGSL helper-side emu-64 ArrayView fn-param raw u32 storage (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Closes Tuvok's local.12 walker WebGPU `EncodeFrameBody_*` arg type mismatch at WGSL L44452 ("expected ptr&lt;array&lt;vec2&lt;u32&gt;&gt;&gt;, got ptr&lt;array&lt;u32&gt;&gt;"). The kernel binds emu-i64 ArrayView as `array&lt;u32&gt;` (raw bits storage — see WGSLKernelFunctionGenerator GenerateHeader line 1899-1903; required for spinlock-protected emu-i64 atomic ops which need per-u32-half access). Pre-fix the helper signature emitted `array&lt;emu_i64&gt;` (= `array&lt;vec2&lt;u32&gt;&gt;`) from `TypeGenerator[Int64]`, leaving naga to reject the call site as a ptr type mismatch. **Fix**: `WGSLFunctionGenerator.GetWgslViewParamType` now detects emu-i64/u64/f64 element types on storage backing and emits `ptr&lt;storage, array&lt;u32&gt;, read_write&gt;` matching the kernel binding. Helper-side LEA/Load/Store overrides updated to mirror the kernel-side raw u32 stride=2 access pattern: LEA stores `target_base_idx = i*2` and aliases the param ptr as `target`, Load emits `emu_i64((*target)[base_idx], (*target)[base_idx+1])` (or `f64_from_ieee754_bits(...)` for f64), Store emits two u32 writes (or `f64_to_ieee754_bits` split for f64). New `Tests23_I64ArrayView_InHelper_NoCodegenError` regression test (6/7 PASS — WebGPU + WebGPUNoSubgroups + Wasm + CPU + CUDA + OpenCL; WebGL skip per existing fn-def-with-pointer GLSL gap). v4.9.5-local.12: WebGPU Group.DimX extent clamp + WebGL explicit-launch body-struct kernel param offset fix (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Three related fixes closing the last open Tests23 sweep failures. **(1) WebGPU Group.DimX extent clamp (closes `Tests23_GroupDimX_Clamps_To_Extent_OnUnitDispatch` on WebGPU + WebGPUNoSubgroups)**: ILGPU's IL clamps groupDim.X = min(extent, customGroupSize) for auto-grouped kernels — pre-fix on CUDA / OpenCL the auto-grouped block size could be 32/64/128/256 from `cuOccupancyMaxPotentialBlockSize`. WebGPU's `@workgroup_size` attribute is fixed at compile time, so we can't change the actual workgroup size per-dispatch without pipeline cache invalidation. Instead, override `WGSLKernelFunctionGenerator.GenerateCode(GroupDimensionValue)` for the X dim of auto-grouped kernels (where `_ilgpu_user_dim` override constant is declared) to emit `i32(min(workgroup_size.x, _ilgpu_user_dim))`. The existing OOB range check at top of main() already keeps excess threads from running; this just exposes the IL-clamped value to user code via Group.DimX consistently with CUDA / OpenCL post-fix semantics. Y/Z dims and explicitly-grouped kernels fall through to the base `i32(workgroup_size.{dim})` emit. **(2) WebGL `KernelParamOffset` dynamic detection (closes `Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody_ExplicitOneByOne_NoLaunchFailure` on WebGL)**: GLSLKernelFunctionGenerator hardcoded `KernelParamOffset = 1` always, treating Method.Parameters[0] as the implicit thread index. For explicitly-launched kernels (LoadStreamKernel&lt;TParam&gt; with KernelConfig + non-Index first arg) and grid-stride (LongIndex1D-first) kernels, the first param is a USER param, not the index. Pre-fix WebGL skipped param[0] entirely → body struct unbound → kernel body referenced undeclared `_idx.field_0` → GLSL compile error. Mirrors `WGSLKernelFunctionGenerator.KernelParamOffset` dynamic logic: returns 0 for IndexType.None / KernelConfig+non-Index, 1 for auto-grouped / KernelConfig+Index. **(3) WebGL `glslParamOffset` host marshaling alignment**: `WebGLAccelerator.MarshalArguments` had `const int glslParamOffset = 1;` matching the old hardcoded codegen. Made dynamic to mirror the codegen change — same logic (0 for IndexType.None / KernelConfig+non-Index, 1 otherwise). Without this alignment, host-side args[0] would map to a different GLSL binding than the kernel expected, leaving body-struct field bindings unfilled (texelFetch returns zero — `RegisterHeavyBody explicit (1,1): expected 5194 got 0` correctness regression). Plus `Tests23_LongOffset_OnSubWordView_NoCodegenError` and `Tests23_I64Shift_InHelper_NoCodegenError` skip on WebGL (matching existing `Tests23_DecodeUint_LongForm_CompileSmoke` skip pattern: GLSL ES 3.0 has no pointer types, ArrayView fn-params can't go through standalone fn defs). PMT verification: 4/4 targeted tests PASS — WebGPU GroupDimX × 2 backends + WebGL/Wasm RegisterHeavyBody_ExplicitOneByOne. v4.9.5-local.11: WGSL helper-side multi-block code-gen — cross-case substitution for complex pointer LEAs (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Closes Tuvok's local.10 walker WebGPU `unresolved value v_X` at Naga compile (`004_EncodeFrameKernel.wgsl` line 22029) for kernels whose helper fns use the multi-block `loop { switch (current_block) { case N: ... } }` state-machine layout. The base `WGSLCodeGenerator.GenerateCode()` post-process already converted simple `let v_X = expr;` lines to function-scope `var` + assignments, but explicitly skipped complex pointer LEAs of the form `let v_X = &amp;(*v_Y)[idx];` because `idx` could reference a block-local. When such a let was declared in `case 0` and `*v_X` was read or written in `case 181`, the let died with its case scope and Naga errored. Fix: SECOND PASS in the post-process scans surviving `let v_X = &amp;expr;` matches and text-substitutes every `*v_X` use with `(&lt;expr&gt;)`. The substitution is sound when the deref target (e.g. `(*v_Y)`) and index (e.g. `i64_to_i32(v_74)`) reference fn parameters or function-scope hoisted vars — both visible from any case. Original `let` lines stay in place to keep any non-deref use of `v_X` (e.g. passing as a pointer arg) resolving inside its own case scope. **Bug context**: Tuvok mis-diagnosed local.10 as a name collision (`var v_76 : i32` vs `let v_76 = &amp;...`); the dump confirms both occurrences are in DIFFERENT WGSL helper fns (`EmitPartitionCdfBoundary_1139883` and `EncodeFrameBody_1139881`), so they don't actually collide — the real bug is the cross-case `let` scope death described above. v4.9.5-local.10: WGSL Bug D phase 7 — helper-side sub-word LEA cross-block hoist + body-struct sub-word LEA cross-block hoist + helper signature address-space monomorphization (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Three related WebGPU codegen fixes for kernels with NoInlining helpers and shared-memory ArrayViews. **(1) Helper-side sub-word LEA cross-block hoist (closes Tuvok local.9 walker WGSL `unresolved value v_X` in deeper helper-emitted code paths)**: `WGSLFunctionGenerator.GenerateCode(LoadElementAddress)` sub-word path was emitting `var v_X : i32 = ...;` BLOCK-scoped — for multi-block helpers (nested if/else/loop within fn body, e.g. recursive partition tree in AV1 walker), cross-block uses fail Naga validation. Fix: when `Method.Blocks.Count > 1`, hoist `var v_X : i32;` to the helper fn body root via deferred-decl insertion (`_helperDeferredVarDeclarations` collected during body emit + `Builder.Insert` injected at saved fn-body start position). **(2) Body-struct sub-word LEA cross-block hoist**: same pattern applied to the body-struct sub-word LEA path at `WGSLKernelFunctionGenerator` line 4672 (mirrors the direct-param sub-word LEA hoist from local.9). **(3) Helper signature address-space monomorphization (Bug D phase 7)**: kernel constructor scans MethodCall sites for `ViewType` args with `AddressSpaceType.Shared` / `Local` and records the observed address space in shared `GeneratorArgs.HelperParamAddressSpaces` dict. Helper's `GetWgslViewParamType` reads from this dict to override the WGSL ptr storage class — closes the helper signature mismatch where ILGPU IR doesn't propagate `Shared` into the helper's parameter type and the signature defaults to `ptr&lt;storage, ...&gt;` while caller passes `ptr&lt;workgroup, ...&gt;`. Unblocks Data's MatMul `TiledMatMulInnerAccumulate` shape (shared-memory ArrayView in helper). PMT regression: 38 pass + 2 WebGL pre-existing fail + 2 WebGL skip = 42/42 (no break on Bug D smoke + body-struct + direct-param coalesce).

v4.9.5-local.9: WGSL sub-word LEA cross-block hoist + base BinaryArithmetic emu_i64 dispatch (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Two related codegen fixes for kernels with NoInlining helpers using sub-word ArrayViews. **(1) Sub-word LEA cross-block hoist (closes Tuvok's local.8 walker WebGPU `unresolved value v_359` at WGSL L19170)**: sub-word LEA emit was `var v_X : i32 = ...;` which is block-scoped in WGSL. When the LEA result is consumed in a different basic block (HoistCrossBlockVariables added the IR Value to `_crossBlockPointers`), Naga rejected the unresolved var name. The pre-existing cross-block fallback registered an inline expression, but the SUB-WORD Load path uses `idx = source.ToString()` directly without checking that dict, so substitution never fired for sub-word. Fix: when LEA value is in `_crossBlockPointers` AND we're in deferred-decl mode, emit `var v_X : i32;` to function-scope deferred declaration list and emit only `v_X = adjustedOffsetExpr;` locally. **(2) Base BinaryArithmetic emu_i64 dispatch**: WGSLCodeGenerator.GenerateBinOp now routes emu_i64/emu_u64 LHS through `i64_add` / `i64_sub` / `i64_mul` / `u64_mul` / `i64_and` / `i64_or` / `i64_xor` (Shl/Shr/Min/Max already had own branches). Without this, helpers using `long a + long b` emit `vec2&lt;u32&gt; + vec2&lt;u32&gt;` which is component-wise (no carry propagation) — semantically WRONG. Defensive — Tuvok's walker doesn't currently exercise emu_i64 Add/Sub/Mul in helpers but any future helper would have hit this. Direct-param coalesce v1+v2 + LEA i64 wrap + i64 shift dispatch + Bug D smoke regression all intact (38 pass + 2 WebGL pre-existing fail).

v4.9.5-local.8: WGSL i64 emulation shift dispatch (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Closes Tuvok's local.7 walker NEW WebGPU failure: `vec2&lt;u32&gt; &gt;&gt; u32` Naga overload mismatch from `long cdfBase &gt;&gt; n` in helper. BinaryArithmetic shift codegen now detects `TypeGenerator[value.Left.Type] == "emu_i64" / "emu_u64"` and routes through `i64_shl` / `i64_shr` / `u64_shr` emulation helpers instead of emitting raw `&gt;&gt;` on vec2&lt;u32&gt; (which WGSL doesn't support — only `T &gt;&gt; u32` for scalar T or `vecN&lt;T&gt; &gt;&gt; vecN&lt;u32&gt;`). New `Tests23_I64Shift_InHelper_NoCodegenError` locks the shape down (6/7 PASS, WebGL skip per existing fn-def-with-pointer GLSL gap). LEA i64 wrap (local.7) + direct-param coalesce v1+v2 (local.6) regression intact. **Bug D phase 7 (AddressSpaceCast variable typing for shared-memory ArrayView passed to NoInlining helpers) tracked as deferred** — needs HoistCrossBlockVariables coordination beyond the AddressSpaceCast emit; doesn't affect Tuvok's walker but blocks Data's MatMul TiledMatMulInnerAccumulate.

v4.9.5-local.7: WGSL helper-side LEA i64 offset wrap + Bug D phase 6 fn-def shared-memory address space (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Two related WebGPU codegen fixes for kernels that pass ArrayView args to NoInlining helpers. **(1) i64 offset wrap** — `WGSLFunctionGenerator.GenerateCode(LoadElementAddress)` (helper-side LEA) now mirrors the kernel-side wrap at line 4445 of `WGSLKernelFunctionGenerator`: detect `value.Offset.Resolve().BasicValueType == BasicValueType.Int64` and emit `i64_to_i32(offset)` before using in both the sub-word `var i32 = ...` and full-word `&amp;(*src)[idx]` paths. Closes Tuvok's local.6 AV1 walker WebGPU failure where `consts[cdfBase + N]` (with `long cdfBase`) emitted `var v_X : i32 = v_Y;` where v_Y was emu_i64 (vec2&lt;u32&gt;). New `Tests23_LongOffset_OnSubWordView_NoCodegenError` locks down the shape; 6/7 PASS (WebGPU + WebGPUNoSubgroups + Wasm + CPU + CUDA + OpenCL; WebGL skip per existing fn-def-with-pointer GLSL gap). **(2) fn-def shared-memory address space** — `WGSLFunctionGenerator.GetWgslViewParamType` now reads `viewType.AddressSpace` and emits the matching WGSL storage class (Shared -&gt; workgroup, Local -&gt; function, Generic/Global -&gt; storage). Sub-word coalesce path stays storage-only since workgroup-memory sub-word views need different layout. Note: shared-memory ArrayView passed to a NoInlining helper still hits a separate AddressSpaceCast variable-typing issue in the kernel (target.Type = element-type instead of pointer-type) — tracked as Bug D phase 7 (separate IR Variable typing fix needed). Existing fn-def smoke + body-struct + direct-param coalesce regression all intact.

v4.9.5-local.6: WebGPU direct-param coalesce v2 — sub-word (Int8/UInt8/Int16/UInt16/Float16-emulated) ArrayView kernel parameters (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Extends local.5 v1 (i32/u32/f32) coalesce to sub-word types so kernels with many same-byte-size sub-word direct ArrayView inputs can fit under WebGPU's `maxStorageBuffersPerShaderStage=10`. Tuvok's AV1 walker `EncodeFrameKernel` now coalesces 5 `ArrayView&lt;byte&gt;` -> 1 binding + groups same-byte-size short/ushort -> 1 binding, dropping raw count from 11 to ~6. **Eligibility (v2 = v1 + sub-word)**: ArrayView (1D), not atomic, not output (per `_directParamOutputs`), not emu-64. Sub-word groups bucket by element type (Int8 / Int16 / Float16-emulated); shared binding storage class is `array&lt;atomic&lt;u32&gt;&gt;` matching existing direct sub-word direct-param storage. **Per-member offset stored as ELEMENT count** (`runningByteOffset / SubWordElementByteSize`) for sub-word groups, vs u32-slot offset for v1 groups — matches each path's WGSL formula (`(elemIdx / elemsPerWord)` for sub-word Load, `binding[u32SlotOffset + i]` for v1). **Sub-word LEA path reused** — DecideCoalesceGroups registers `_subWordParams[paramIdx]=elemSize` and `_subWordBodyStructBindingNames[paramIdx]=leaderBindingName`; the existing sub-word LEA + Load codegen (atomicLoad + shift + mask + sign/zero-extend) finds the leader's binding via the same dict that serves body-struct sub-word coalesce members. **Bucket logic fix** — initial implementation routed Int8/Int16 ArrayViews to the i32/u32/f32 bucket because `TypeGenerator[Int8]` returns `"i32"` (WGSL has no i8 type); fixed by checking `BasicValueType` for sub-word FIRST, falling back to `wgslElem` only for non-sub-word types. **Test** — new `Tests21_DirectParam_11ArrayViewByte_CoalesceTest` (full-sum 11×256 byte inputs + i32 output, 11 byte ArrayViews coalesced into 1 binding, total 3 bindings) + `_PerInputDiagnostic` (per-byte zero-extend correctness with byte values 7..77 each). 52/56 PMT pass on WebGPU + WebGPUNoSubgroups + Wasm + CPU + CUDA + OpenCL (4 expected WebGL skips for body-struct tests not applicable to direct-param). v1 i32 + body-struct coalesce regression intact. **Unblocks Tuvok's AV1 walker** `phase1-walker-debug` branch on WebGPU.

v4.9.5-local.5: WebGPU direct-param coalesce v1 — i32/u32/f32 ArrayView kernel parameters (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Mirror of body-struct coalesce for kernels that take many SAME-TYPED, INPUT-ONLY direct `ArrayView&lt;int&gt;` / `&lt;uint&gt;` / `&lt;float&gt;` parameters that would push raw bindings over WebGPU's `maxStorageBuffersPerShaderStage` (Chrome=10). When raw count &gt; threshold, same-typed input-only direct ArrayView params are coalesced into a single shared storage binding; per-member u32-slot offsets travel through `_scalar_params`, the `LoadElementAddress` emit redirects to `&amp;{leader}[i32(_scalar_params[voSlot]) + offset]`. New `Tests21_DirectParam_13ArrayViewInt_CoalesceTest` and `_PerInputDiagnostic` lock down full-sum + per-input correctness; body-struct coalesce regression (12-int + Mixed + VariableLength + per-field diagnostic) all green on WebGPU after the change. Lifts the "11 storage buffer bindings, device max 10" wall for kernels with multiple same-typed i32/u32/f32 inputs. Sub-word (byte/sbyte/short/ushort/Half) and emu-64 (long/double) direct params remain excluded from v1 coalesce — they need separate path (different binding storage class for sub-word, different stride emit for emu-64). Tracked as v2.

v4.9.5-local.4: Wasm explicit-launch body-struct kernel marshaling fix (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Closes `Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody_ExplicitOneByOne_NoLaunchFailure` MarshalDirectiveException on `ILGPU.Util.DisposeBase`. `WasmKernelFunctionGenerator.SetupParameters` was mis-detecting explicit-launch kernels with multi-view body-struct first param as having an implicit Index — the body's parameter loop never ran, paramInfos stayed empty, and the dispatcher's struct-serialization fallback hit `Marshal.StructureToPtr` which failed on ArrayView&lt;T&gt;'s class-reference Buffer field. Fix: new `LooksLikeIndexType` shape check requires parameters[0] to actually match the IndexType dimensionality (PrimitiveType for Index1D/KernelConfig, StructureType with N Int32 fields for Index2D/Index3D). Plus replaced `Marshal.StructureToPtr` with `Unsafe.Write` everywhere (defense in depth). 8/8 regression sweep PASS including 3 RegisterHeavyBody variants + Bug D smoke + RadixSort pairs/non-pairs + HostWriteRace.

v4.9.5-local.3: Wasm lazy per-HWC snapshot tier (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Fixes RadixSort multi-pass data-corruption regression (TJ report 2026-05-05; `WasmTests.AlgorithmRadixSortNonPairs{Int,Float}Test` returned input order unchanged) AND restores Data's StyleMosaic ML-weight-reuse perf in one mechanism. Eager queue-time snapshots replaced with lazy capture: at RunKernel sync, each arg buffer registers a dispatch intent recording HostWriteCounter (no bytes copied). At any host-write path, `PrepareHostWrite` captures the CURRENT SharedBuffer into a per-HWC tier ONLY if pending intents exist (refcount = pending-intent count at materialization). At copy-IN, dispatch reads from its qhwc tier iff host wrote since queue; otherwise reads SharedBuffer directly. At copy-OUT, buffers whose copy-IN read from a snapshot have their copy-OUT skipped (preserves the host write that newer dispatches need). At dispatch completion, the tier's refcount is decremented; SAB released when last referencer completes. Multi-pass RadixSort: no host writes -> no snapshots, every pass reads prior pass's copy-OUT via SharedBuffer. ML weight reuse: weights uploaded once with no pending intents -> no snapshot. Host-write race: snapshot tier captured pre-write for D1; D2 (queued post-write) reads SharedBuffer (preserved by D1's skipped copy-OUT). Verified RadixSort{NonPairs,Pairs,Descending,Algorithm,Threshold,Boundary,RepeatedResort,SpawnSceneSimulation,1.4M,2M,4M} + Tests23_HostWriteVsQueuedDispatchRace + body-struct + sub-word sweep all green.

v4.9.5-local.2: Wasm linear memory drops 100% margin (LOCAL FEED ONLY). `WasmAccelerator.RunKernelAsync` was computing `wasmPages = ceil(totalWithBarriers / 65536) * 2` — doubling every linear-memory request as a "100% margin." The exact `totalWithBarriers` already accounts for every region (buffers + per-thread/per-worker scratch + struct + shared memory + barriers + fence + per-worker yield state); the doubling was gratuitous defensive padding originally added when worker count grew from a hardcoded 4 to `navigator.hardwareConcurrency`. For ML workloads (Data's StyleMosaic_DiagnosticPerOpSync 102 dispatches) where a single dispatch's actual layout exceeds ~1 GiB, the doubled request crossed the browser's 2 GiB SharedArrayBuffer cap and `WebAssembly.Memory.grow()` rejected with `RangeError: Maximum memory size exceeded`. Replaced with a 1-page (64 KB) absolute pad that absorbs any single-byte miscalculation without doubling the footprint. Effective cap usage drops from `~totalLayout / 2` to `~totalLayout - 64 KB`. Plus VerboseLogging-gated per-dispatch / init / grow / reuse logs with full layout context, and OutOfMemoryException now includes the cap value. Pre-existing failures NOT introduced by this change (verified by running tests on master before this commit): WasmTests.AlgorithmRadixSortNonPairs{Int,Float}Test (data corruption, separate root cause), WasmTests.Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody_ExplicitOneByOne_NoLaunchFailure (MarshalDirectiveException, separate root cause).

v4.9.5-local.1: WGSL Bug D phases 2/3/5 + Tuvok's i64 emulation-library scan fix (LOCAL FEED ONLY). Sub-word ArrayView fn-params (byte/sbyte/short/ushort/Half) now flow through standalone-fn-def helpers on WebGPU - WGSLFunctionGenerator overrides LoadElementAddress / Load / Store to emit the kernel's atomicLoad+shift+mask+sign-extend chain with the helper's local ptr alias as the binding. Helper-to-helper non-inline calls now emit a real WGSL fn call (was "Unmapped fallback"). Cross-block field address inline substitution, AddressSpaceCast on local alloca, GLSL function-return struct constructor, and WebGL struct-defs ordering also landed. **Tuvok's blocker fix:** SetEmulationFlags() and ScanForSubgroupAndBroadcastUsage() now walk a unified EnumerateAllHelperMethods() that includes BOTH Inline and NoInline helpers via a new GeneratorArgs.NonInlineMethods list - closes the AV1 walker symptom where a NoInlining helper's `long cdfBase` / `state.Low` u64 ops produced WGSL i64_ge / i64_eq calls without their emulation definitions. Tests23_DecodeUint_LongForm_CompileSmoke: 6/7 pass (WebGPU 622ms, WebGPUNoSubgroups 213ms, Wasm 272ms, CPU + CUDA + OpenCL pass), WebGL skipped via UnsupportedTestException (GLSL ES has no pointer types - ArrayView fn-params can't go through standalone fn defs; tracked as Bug D follow-up).

v4.9.5-rc.27: WebGPU coalesce excludes OUTPUT body-struct view fields. When a body struct contains an output view (e.g. `Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody { ArrayView&lt;int&gt; A0..A10; ArrayView&lt;int&gt; Out; }` where Out is the kernel write target), pre-rc.27 coalesce bundled all 12 same-typed views (A0..A10 + Out) into a single shared GPU buffer. The host concatenated INPUT data into the shared buffer at dispatch time but never copied data BACK to the original output ArrayView's GPU storage — so kernel writes to Out[0] landed in the shared INPUT buffer instead of bOut, and the test read 0 from bOut instead of the expected sum (5194). New `ScanForBodyStructOutputs` walks every Store / GenericAtomic / AtomicCAS in the kernel and helper methods, identifies body-struct view fields that are write targets, and `DecideCoalesceGroups` excludes them. **Closes** `WebGPUTests.Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody_UnitExtent_NoLaunchFailure` and `WebGPUNoSubgroupsTests.Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody_UnitExtent_NoLaunchFailure`. 42/42 PMT body-struct sweep PASS across all backends. 14/14 desktop regression PASS.

v4.9.5-rc.26: WebGL body-struct codegen — closes the rc.25 v2 follow-ups, all 8 Tests23 body-struct tests now PASS on WebGL. Two additional fixes: (1) **Single-view body struct unwrap** — when a kernel parameter is a struct holding exactly one `ArrayView&lt;T&gt;` field (e.g. `Tests23_OnlyShortStruct { ArrayView&lt;short&gt; S0 }`), ILGPU's IR pre-transforms the param to the inner `ViewType&lt;T&gt;` directly, leaving the host side passing a struct value mismatched against a single-sampler kernel. `WebGLAccelerator.MarshalArguments` now walks struct args with no `BaseView` property; if the struct has exactly one IArrayView field it unwraps to that view, mirroring the IR transform. (2) **ArrayView1D wrapper metadata fields always intercepted** — a body struct of `ArrayView1D&lt;T, Stride1D.Dense&gt;` fields flattens in IR to (View, Int64-length, optional Int8-flag) per wrapper. Pre-rc.26 the codegen state machine used WGSL's `isLastField` heuristic to disambiguate length-vs-reduce-value, but in GLSL the standard `GenerateCode(GetField)` fallthrough then emitted `u_param{N}_stride[0]` for unmatched metadata fields — undeclared and broke compile. rc.26 unconditionally marks Int64-after-View as IsViewMetadata, the GetField hook intercepts all metadata fields and emits a length-uniform reference using the associated view's binding name (so `u_param{N}_f{metadata_fi}_length` aliases to `u_param{N}_f{view_fi}_length` which is actually declared). Together these close `Tests23_OnlyShortBodyStruct` and `Tests23_TwoShortBodyStructDense`. **All 8/8 WebGL body-struct tests PASS** including Tuvok's `Tests23_SilkBodyStructShape`. 12/12 desktop sweep clean (CUDA + OpenCL + CPU).

v4.9.5-rc.25: WebGL multi-view body-struct kernel parameter codegen (#26 partial close). When a kernel takes a struct parameter whose fields include 2+ `ArrayView&lt;T&gt;` (e.g. `Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody` with 12 ArrayView&lt;int&gt;, or Tuvok's `SilkDecodeCoreInputs` with 6 short + 9 int views), WebGL/GLSL now decomposes the body struct into per-field sampler bindings. Previous behavior: every field aliased the same single sampler, output was silently wrong. New behavior: each ArrayView field gets its own `u_param{N}_f{M}` sampler binding via a synthetic param-index encoding `(paramIdx+1)*1000 + fieldIdx`. Mirrors the WGSL pattern that shipped in rc.17/rc.18. **Verified PASSING on WebGL**: `Tests23_TwoShortBodyStruct`, `Tests23_SilkBodyStructShape` (Tuvok's actual 6 short + 9 int shape), `Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody_UnitExtent_NoLaunchFailure`, `Tests23_MinimalShortIntBodyStruct`, `Tests23_MinimalShortIntBodyStruct_IntOnly`, `Tests23_DeepUnroll_NoLaunchFailure`. **Known v2 follow-ups (still failing)**: `Tests23_OnlyShortBodyStruct` (single `ArrayView&lt;short&gt;` body field — buffer bind path issue) and `Tests23_TwoShortBodyStructDense` (`ArrayView1D&lt;T, Stride1D.Dense&gt;` body fields — IR multi-dim view path conflict). Workaround for both: use raw `ArrayView&lt;T&gt;` body fields with 2+ views, or pass single ArrayView as direct kernel param (not wrapped in struct).

v4.9.5-rc.24: CUDA body-struct ArrayView-field alignment ROOT-CAUSE FIX (#32 closed) + module-load diagnostics. (1) `IR.Types.ViewType.Alignment` was hardcoded to 4, so a body struct containing 2+ `ArrayView&lt;T&gt;` fields was emitted as `.param .align 4 .b8 _s_91[32]` in PTX. The host-side argument buffer was laid out at 8-byte alignment (each ArrayView field lowers to ViewImplementation = void* + long = 8-byte-aligned 16-byte struct), so the kernel signature alignment didn't match the buffer, and CUDA rejected the launch with `CUDA_ERROR_LAUNCH_OUT_OF_RESOURCES` even at blockDim=1 — even though ptxas reported NUM_REGS=24, no spilling, no shared/local mem, MAX_THREADS_PER_BLOCK=1024. Single-ArrayView body structs and `ArrayView1D&lt;T, Stride1D.Dense&gt;` (which wraps the view in a StructureType) didn't trip the bug because their alignment propagated correctly via different paths. Fix: `ViewType` now mirrors `PointerType` — `Size = Alignment = 8` on 64-bit targets, 4 on 32-bit. Closes Tuvok's SilkDecodeCoreGpu CUDA bug (Tests23_SilkBodyStructShape, Tests23_TwoShortBodyStruct, Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody_UnitExtent_NoLaunchFailure, Tests23_RegisterHeavyBody_LargeExtent_Parallel all PASS post-fix on CUDA). (2) `CU_JIT_MAX_REGISTERS=255` cap added to `cuModuleLoadDataEx` (defense in depth — forces ptxas to spill instead of producing kernels that exceed the per-thread hardware cap on any sm_50+ device). Configurable via `CudaAccelerator.DefaultMaxRegistersPerThread` (default 255, set 0 to disable). (3) `CU_JIT_INFO_LOG_BUFFER` + `CU_JIT_LOG_VERBOSE` + `cuFuncGetAttribute` diagnostic plumbing — surfaces ptxas register/spill info and `MAX_THREADS_PER_BLOCK / NUM_REGS / SHARED_SIZE_BYTES / LOCAL_SIZE_BYTES / CONST_SIZE_BYTES / PTX_VERSION / BINARY_VERSION` per loaded kernel via `Trace.WriteLine` when `CudaAccelerator.VerboseModuleLoad = true` (off by default). (4) New regression `Tests23_DeepUnroll_NoLaunchFailure` locks down deep-unroll register-pressure shape across all backends.

v4.9.5-rc.23: Wasm dispatcher watchdog timeout. If worker tasks don't all complete within `WasmAccelerator.WasmDispatchWatchdogSeconds` (default 120s, set 0 to disable), throw a `TimeoutException` with kernel name, dispatch number, and completion ratio. Defense in depth atop rc.21's fast-fault — catches kernels that infinite-loop without erroring. Surfaced 2026-05-04 by Data's StyleMosaic Wasm hang where the kernel didn't trap, just never posted back.

v4.9.5-rc.22: WebGL runtime-safe Pow for negative base + buffer-loaded exponent. ONNX LayerNorm `(x-mean)^pow_initializer_2.0` has the exponent loaded from an ArrayView; static-const detection (rc.12) doesn't catch. Adds runtime-safe wrapper `(x>=0?pow(x,y):pow(abs(x),y)*(mod(y,2)>=1?-1:1))` for the buffer-loaded-exponent case. Closes Data's DistilBERT + SemanticSearch WebGL drift.

v4.9.5-rc.21: Wasm dispatcher fast-fault on first worker error + kernel name in error. `Task.WhenAll(workerTasks)` waited for ALL workers before throwing; one trap with others blocked = 10-min hang. Replaced with `Task.WhenAny` drain loop that throws on first faulted task. Worker error message now includes `kernel=&lt;name&gt;` so crew can identify the trapping op without per-dispatch diagnostic logging.

v4.9.5-rc.20: Wasm per-kernel worker module cache. Multi-kernel pipelines (ML inference: Conv2D / InstanceNorm / ReLU alternating) used to invalidate the worker-side `_cachedModule` on every kernel switch — 100 dispatches × 6 kernel types × 8 workers = ~4800 Wasm module re-compiles. Per-kernel cache: each (worker, kernel) compiles once and stays cached. Key: `kernelId = RuntimeHelpers.GetHashCode(wasmBytes)`.

v4.9.5-rc.19: WebGPU `WGSLTypeGenerator.GenerateTypeDefinitions` concurrent-modification fix. Iterating `mapping` while `this[fieldType]` lazily registered new types caused `InvalidOperationException: InvalidOperation_EnumFailedVersion`. Snapshot+drain pattern.

v4.9.5-rc.18: WebGPU WGSL IsMultiDim discriminates body struct from single ArrayView wrapper. A body struct with 2 × ArrayView1D = 6 IR fields was misclassified as 3D ArrayView; both views aliased to the same binding. Count actual ViewType fields to disambiguate.

v4.9.5-rc.17: WebGPU sub-word body-struct coalesce fix (closes Tuvok's SilkDecodeCoreGpu on WebGPU - task #33). `DecideCoalesceGroups` ran before `_subWordParams` was populated, so sub-word fields got bundled into a non-atomic int coalesce bucket and `atomicLoad` rejected the binding. Detect sub-word from `elemType.BasicValueType` directly.

v4.9.5-rc.16: Wasm snapshot invalidation perf — limit `_gpuWriteSeq` bump to actually-written buffers. Read-only ML weight buffers were being re-snapshotted every dispatch; 50MB × 100 dispatches = 5GB of wasted copies. Gate on `writtenBufferIndices.Contains(i)`.

v4.9.5-rc.15: Wasm dispatcher diagnostic typed-array allocations gated behind VerboseLogging. Hardcoded `length=4` in a debug block crashed sub-word body-struct kernels on first dispatch (when `bufferInfos[0]` was 2-byte short).

v4.9.5-rc.14: WebGL kernel-main override gets the Div/Rem unsigned cast and Pow neg-base int-exp expansion (the rc.12/rc.13 fixes only landed in the helper-function base; kernel-main override needed the same).

v4.9.5-rc.13: Two correctness fixes - Wasm dispatcher snapshot regression (BlazeFace/DDPM zero outputs at rc.11) + WGSL unsigned Div/Rem on i32-as-uint (closes DecodeUint on WebGPU).

v4.9.5-rc.12: WebGL GLSL Pow neg-base + integer exponent expansion (closes Data's DistilBERT/SemanticSearch/GPT-2 cluster) + WebGPU WGSL Shr/Shl signed-shift on i32-as-uint (closes Tuvok's DecodeBitLogP).

v4.9.5-rc.11: Wasm host-write-vs-queued-dispatch race fix. Snapshot SharedBuffer at queue time so D1's copy-IN reads its own data even if D2 host-overwrote between queues.

v4.9.5-rc.10: WebGL `glWorker.js` SubView-offset uniform leak across same-program dispatches (closes Data's StyleMosaic Gather + 11 ML cascade closures) + Wasm OOB diagnostic correctness (per-view element size tracking).

For older rc release notes, see git log on master and `_DevComms/global/nuget-local-publish-log.md`.</PackageReleaseNotes>
